How would you design a future cityscape with COVID-19 in mind? Our students from the Smart-City Management and Technology programme placed citizen wellness front-and-centre as they harnessed data analytics and public sentiment to help develop smart public spaces for the Urban Redevelopment Authority (URA).&nbsp;
&nbsp;
By conducting surveys and analysing the results to define what the public perceives as safety in public spaces, the group of Year 3 students — Brendan Ong Sin Kai, Chong Yun Yu, Christal Poon, Heng Bing Chow, Jeff Lim Shen Jie and Jessica Low Hui Chen — employed tools picked up in the Analytics Applications in Smart Living module to propose approaches to URA for the design of public spaces in Paya Lebar Central.
&nbsp;
Read More: smu.sg/smart-city-tools-battling-pandemic
