The gradual assimilation of data analytics with the legal industry is perhaps the most significant change that has taken place in the legal sector over the last few years. At SMU, the ways in which law is being taught has also evolved.

Jointly offered by the SMU School of Law and SMU School of Computing and Information Systems, the Bachelor of Science (Computing and Law) degree is a single integrated specialist degree that has subjects curated for the contextualisation of law and technology and vice versa. Graduates of the Computing and Law degree have access to a wide array of careers, from legal technologists to even engineers and appeals across industries.
&nbsp;
Learn more at smu.edu.sg/bsc-computing-law
