SIS alumnus Anders Tan shared how studying at the Institute of Technical Education helped him turn his life around and set him on a journey to help others. In 2013, during his final year at SMU, he co-founded social enterprise EduSnap, which employed people with disabilities (PWDs) as virtual tutors for needy students. Following which, he started software development agency Bit Studio. In 2018, he and a partner started Inclus, a social business that helps young PWDs transition to adulthood with gainful employment and independent living.
